2500|$|In Canada, work {{to reduce}} the effects of acid mine {{drainage}} is concentrated under the Mine Environment Neutral Drainage (MEND) program. Total liability from <b>acid</b> <b>rock</b> <b>drainage</b> {{is estimated to be}} between $2 billion and $5 billion CAD. [...] Over a period of eight years, MEND claims to have reduced ARD liability by up to $400 million CAD, from an investment of $17.5 million CAD.|$|E
